# --- PyInstaller / desktop build artifacts ---
# PyInstaller writes a top-level `<AppName>.spec` next to pyproject.toml on
# every build. We never commit those — committed PyInstaller specs live
# under packaging/<os>/ and are explicitly tracked. The pattern below is
# anchored to the repo root on purpose; `packaging/**/*.spec` is unaffected.
/*.spec
*.spec.bak
*.dmg
*.pkg
*.exe
*.msi
*.AppImage
src-pyloid/build/
src-pyloid/dist/
dist/

# --- Local data + runtime artifacts ---
# `data/` covers the web runtime root (uploads, snapshots, user models).
# IMPORTANT: do NOT add an unanchored `storage/`, `runs/` (as a bare line),
# or similar pattern back here — anchored matches are mandatory. An earlier
# template's unanchored `storage/` silently matched a `storage/` directory
# inside the source tree and broke CI for two days. Always lead with `/` or
# `<dirname>/` rooted at a known source path.
data/
datasets/
*.sqlite
*.sqlite3
*.db
*.joblib
*.parquet

# --- YOLO / Ultralytics runtime output ---
# Ultralytics writes training runs to ./runs/ by default. We override this
# to the user's storage_root in the backend, but anchor the ignore anyway
# for accidental dev runs that fall back to the default.
/runs/
/wandb/
/weights/

# --- Bundled model weights ---
# Per PLAN.md §7, eight starter weights (~80 MB) ship inside the binary.
# They are downloaded by scripts/fetch-models.py (added in P0.7) on first
# build, NOT committed to git. The `models/<task>/.gitkeep` files keep the
# directory structure alive.
models/detect/*.pt
models/classify/*.pt
models/detect/*.onnx
models/classify/*.onnx
!models/**/.gitkeep

